(148,	'en_us',	'Page',	23,	'content',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">Once your account has been funded, you can begin to place bets. Here is how you will go about it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">On the home page, you will see about Sport Menu. There you will see different sport listed that you can play right away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Click on any sport you wan to bet on, click on football to have access to leagues available.</p>\r\n<p>If you want other sports, you can click on the particular sport you want.</p>\r\n<p>Everything is well arranged for easy navigation.</p>\r\n<p>A picture they say is worth a thousand words. Let us take a look like you are ready to bet. Lets click on England to see what comes up.</p>\r\n<p>let us assume you want to choose</p>\r\n<p>Fulham, Tottenham, Man Utd and Chelsea to win. All you have to do is click</p>\r\n<p>on the odds one after the other.</p>\r\n<p>there are always three odds for each matches. the first odd is what you get</p>\r\n<p>if the first team win. The second odd is what you get if the teams draw and the last odd is what you get if the away team win.</p>\r\n<p>In a nutshell, whichever team you want to back to win, just click on the odd. If you think the match will end in a draw, just click on middle odd. It is very easy to do. As you click on your choice, the team selected will be added to your bet slip on the right hand side. See where the arrow the image below is pointing to.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to stake on just a single match, select the match and finish the bet and then select another one if you want to continue. It is when you want to accumulate that you should select more than one match. Anyway, after selecting the matches you want, you can then proceed to bet. Enter the amount you want to bet with in the space provided beside &ldquo;stake&rdquo;. Click on Preview under your bet slip.</p>\r\n<p>Click \"Submit Ticket\" to complete your bet.</p>\r\n<p>I forgot to say that you can accumulate matches from different countries.</p>\r\n<p>In the example above, if you want to add another bet from another country into your accumulator, simply click on the country on the left hand side.</p>\r\n<p>Your bet slip will remain intact. After adding it, you can place your bet.</p>\r\n<p>If you win, your account will be credited within 10 minutes after the matches are played. It\'s that simple.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other Kinds of Bets</strong></p>\r\n<p>We have explained how you can place bets on yourdomain.com. Now, that is just a tip of the iceberg because there are other kinds of bets that are on offer.</p>\r\n<p>For example, you can bet on which team will score the first goal or you can bet on what will be the exact scoreline. You can predict who will win the first half.</p>\r\n<p>There are so many options you can bet on. Let me show you how.</p>\r\n<p>If you look at the matches on display, you will see some options at the top of &nbsp;the matches available.</p>\r\n<p>What this means is that for example in the case ,the matches have other kinds of markets you can bet on.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Using the Fulham match as example, you will notice the bet option available, it will bring up different kinds of bets.&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>If you desire to choose any of the bets, just click on it and it will be added to your bet slip.</div>\r\n<div>If you want to know what those bets mean,</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>EXACT SCORE BET :</strong> it means you want to bet on the the exact number of scores for the match.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>DOUBLE CHANCE BET:</strong> this is an example of double chance bet.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>HANDICAP BET:</strong> this is an example of handicap bet</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>UNDER / OVER BET:</strong> this is when you want to bet on a match, that</div>\r\n<div>the scores will the under or over a certain score.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>How To Check Your Bet History</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>In case you want to take a look at the matches you have played, you can</div>\r\n<div>check your history. Just click on <strong>\"Tickets\"</strong> on the top right of the</div>\r\n<div>site after you have logged in.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>There you can see your transaction history. It includes your won bets, lost</div>\r\n<div>bets, pending bets and whole lot of other stuffs. You can click on each transaction to see it in details.</div>\r\n<div>You can also check your history of deposits and that of payouts.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>How To Withdraw From Your yourdomain.com Account</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>One of the joys of betting on football is winning money and getting paid.</div>\r\n<div>yourdomain.com is the best when it comes to paying winnings.</div>\r\n<div>The first thing you need to do is click on Profile (Ignore this step if you have already included your bank details when you open your account)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Enter the amount you want to withraw and then click on <strong>\"Request Manual Withraw\"</strong>. We will automatically deduct the amount from your account.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Your bank account will be credited within 2 working days.</div>\r\n<div>It could be before but it wont be after.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>This Is Very Important</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>Remember at the beginning where we said you should use your real names to register? It\'s because of your withdrawal. Take note that you are being asked for your bank and account number only. The system is not asking for your account name.That is because the system has your name on file already. If your name is Dele Akinpelu, the account number you should submit should tally with that name. You won\'t be allowed to edit your name. It\'s for your own security.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>'),
