(18,	'lit',	'News',	1,	'content',	'<p>Lionel Messi has been cleared by Barcelona&#39;s team doctors to play in Argentina&#39;s World Cup qualifiers against Colombia and Ecuador.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi pulled his right hamstring on April 2. He aggravated the same injury a few weeks later, sidelining him for the final three weeks of the Spanish league season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After hosting Colombia on Friday, Argentina travels to Ecuador for another qualifier on Tuesday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Argentina leads the South American qualifying group for the 2014 World Cup in Brazil.</p>\r\n'),
